<i>noun</i>: 토굴 [토굴], 동굴 [동ː굴], 굴 [굴ː] <br>
<ul>
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>토굴 [토굴]</dt><br>
<dd>cave; cavern</dd><br>
<dd>땅을 깊고 길게 파서 굴과 같이 만든 큰 구덩이.</dd><br>
<dd>A big, long cave, that is made by digging the ground deeply.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>동굴 [동ː굴]</dt><br>
<dd>cave</dd><br>
<dd>자연적으로 생긴 넓고 깊은 굴.</dd><br>
<dd>A big, deep natural hole in the earth.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>굴 [굴ː]</dt><br>
<dd>1. cave</dd><br>
<dd>땅이나 바위가 안으로 깊고 길게 파인 것.</dd><br>
<dd>A long, deep tunnel dug underground or through rocks.</dd><br>
<dd>2. tunnel</dd><br>
<dd>산이나 땅 속을 뚫어 만든 길.</dd><br>
<dd>A path or road dug through a mountain or underground.</dd><br>
<dd>3. den; hole</dd><br>
<dd>짐승들이 사는 구멍.</dd><br>
<dd>A hole where animals live.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>